dent and discovered that it was a boy of about 11 years, Mustapha Sulaiman, who drowned in a river. “The victim was rescued dead and handed toward the head of Tudun Rubidi, Alh. Danliti Amadu Garba. “Similarly, today (Friday) at about 8:22 am, we received a call from Malam Shehu in Rangaza Inusawa of the same Ungwago local government that a 27years old man, Abubakar Salisu drowned in a river. Upon receiving the information, we dispatched our men to the scene to rescue the victim but unfortunately, the victim was rescued dead. “The corpse was taken to Sir Sunusi General Hospital,” Muhammed however said. Vanguard News A 22-year-old man, Mustapha Musa, has drowned while bathing in a pond at Farawa Ramin Fara in the Tarauni Local Government Area (LGA) of Kano State. April 10, 2019 In "News" A teenage boy identified as Atiku Sani, 16 years old has drowned in a pond in Bachirawa, Ungoggo local government area of Kano State. July 8, 2020 In "Metro" The Kano State Fire Service has confirmed one person killed in a fire incident involving a petrol tanker at Kofar Ruwa area of Kano metropolis. The spokesman of the Service, Mr. Saidu Mohammed, confirmed the incident in a statement on Tuesday in Kano. Mohammed said the incident occurred on Monday… July 29, 2020 In "News"